# Visual Hierarchy

## Size Hierarchy

### Headings
Use clear size progression:
- **H1**: 2-3× body size (32-48px)
- **H2**: 1.75-2× body size (28-36px)
- **H3**: 1.5-1.75× body size (24-28px)
- **H4**: 1.25-1.5× body size (20-24px)
- **H5-H6**: 1-1.25× body size (16-20px)

### Body Text
- **Large body**: 18-20px (landing pages, marketing)
- **Standard body**: 14-16px (applications, content)
- **Small body**: 12-14px (captions, metadata)

## Weight Hierarchy

### Font Weights
- **Headings**: Bold (700) or Semibold (600)
- **Subheadings**: Semibold (600) or Medium (500)
- **Body text**: Regular (400)
- **De-emphasized**: Light (300) or secondary color

## Color Hierarchy

### Text Colors
- **Primary text**: Darkest (high contrast) - main content
- **Secondary text**: Medium gray - supporting content
- **Tertiary text**: Light gray - metadata, captions
- **Disabled text**: Lightest gray - disabled states

Example (light mode):
- Primary: #1a1a1a or gray-900
- Secondary: #525252 or gray-700
- Tertiary: #737373 or gray-600
- Disabled: #a3a3a3 or gray-400

## Spacing Hierarchy

### Vertical Rhythm
- **Between paragraphs**: 1em (16px)
- **Heading to content**: 0.5-1em (8-16px)
- **Section spacing**: 2-4em (32-64px)
- **Page sections**: 4-6em (64-96px)

### Grouping
- **Related elements**: Close spacing (8-12px)
- **Separate groups**: Medium spacing (16-24px)
- **Major sections**: Large spacing (32-48px)

## Action Hierarchy

### Button Emphasis
1. **Primary (highest)**: Filled, brand color - main CTA
2. **Secondary**: Outlined or tonal - alternative actions
3. **Tertiary**: Ghost/text - low-priority actions

### Visual Weight
- **Primary**: Solid background, high contrast
- **Secondary**: Border or subtle background
- **Tertiary**: Text only, minimal styling

## Layout Hierarchy

### Z-Index Layers
- **Base content**: z-index: 0
- **Sticky headers**: z-index: 10
- **Dropdowns/popovers**: z-index: 100
- **Modals/dialogs**: z-index: 1000
- **Toasts/notifications**: z-index: 10000

### Visual Depth
- **Background**: Lowest contrast, recedes
- **Content**: Medium contrast, primary focus
- **Interactive elements**: Highest contrast, forward

## Contrast Hierarchy

### Emphasis Levels
- **High emphasis**: Dark text, solid backgrounds, bold weight
- **Medium emphasis**: Medium gray text, outlined elements
- **Low emphasis**: Light gray text, minimal styling

### Accessibility
- **Primary content**: 4.5:1 contrast minimum
- **Large text (18px+)**: 3:1 contrast minimum
- **Interactive elements**: 3:1 contrast with surrounding

## Practical Application

### Card Hierarchy
```
┌─────────────────────────┐
│ Title (H3, Bold)        │ ← Highest emphasis
│ Subtitle (Body, Gray)   │ ← Medium emphasis
│ Description (Body)      │ ← Standard
│ Metadata (Small, Gray)  │ ← Lowest emphasis
│ [Primary] [Secondary]   │ ← Action hierarchy
└─────────────────────────┘
```

### Page Hierarchy
```
Header (sticky, elevated)
├─ Logo (high emphasis)
├─ Navigation (medium emphasis)
└─ Actions (high emphasis - CTA)

Main Content
├─ H1 (highest emphasis)
├─ Intro paragraph (large, medium emphasis)
├─ H2 Sections (high emphasis)
│  ├─ Body content (standard)
│  └─ Supporting info (low emphasis)
└─ CTA Section (high emphasis)

Footer (low emphasis, recedes)
```

## Common Mistakes

### ❌ Avoid
- All text same size/weight
- No clear primary action
- Everything equally prominent
- Inconsistent heading sizes
- Random emphasis

### ✅ Do
- Clear size progression
- One primary action per section
- Intentional emphasis
- Consistent heading scale
- Purposeful hierarchy
